---
description: 'Git workflow automation and MCP integration for commit consistency'
globs: ['**/*']
alwaysApply: true
rules:
  autoStage: true
  conventionalCommits: true
  branchNaming: 'feature/description'
  commitMessageTemplate: 'type(scope): description'
reviewPrompts:
  - 'Are all commits following the conventional format (e.g., feat(component): add feature)?'
  - 'Are branches named using the agreed convention like feature/login-page?'
  - 'Does the commit message clearly describe what and why the change was made?'
  - 'Are changes auto-staged or manually selected during commit?'
  - 'Is this integrated with the MCP Git server for consistency?'
---